

ðŸ”¹ DFDL Kya hai?

DFDL ek modeling language hai, jiska use hum non-XML data formats (text ya binary) ko define aur parse/serialize karne ke liye karte hain.

Matlab: tumhare paas data hai jo CSV, fixed-length, COBOL copybook, industry standards (SWIFT, EDI, HL7) ya koi bhi legacy format me hai â†’ usko tum XML ke tarah treat karke process karna chahte ho â†’ waha DFDL help karta hai.


ðŸ‘‰ Important:

DFDL data format ko describe karta hai (kaise data banta hai / kaisa dikhta hai).

DFDL khud ek data format nahi hai.



---

ðŸ”¹ DFDL ka Structure

DFDL ka schema actually ek XML Schema (XSD) hota hai jisme annotations hoti hain jo batati hain:

1. Logical format â†’ XSD elements batate hain data ka logical structure (fields, sequences, types).


2. Physical format â†’ DFDL annotations batati hain ki ye fields text hai ya binary, length kitni hai, delimiter kya hai, encoding kya hai, etc.




ðŸ”¹ DFDL Support in IIB

IBM Integration Bus (ya ACE) mai tum DFDL use kar sakte ho:

DFDL parser & domain â†’ Non-XML data ko XML tree me convert karne ke liye.

DFDL serializer â†’ XML tree ko non-XML format me wapas banane ke liye.

Schema editor â†’ Toolkit ke andar graphical way me schema banana.

Testing perspective â†’ Data ko directly test karne ke liye (input/output check).

DFDL API (Java, C) â†’ Agar tum standalone DFDL applications likhna chahte ho.



